		<wp:meta_key><![CDATA[text]]></wp:meta_key>
		<wp:meta_value><![CDATA[The Graz Giants can look forward to a boost to their offense: De'Queze Fryer will be joining the team from the Styrian capital. " I feel incredibly honored to become part of the Graz Giants and to be able to play for this team," Fryer explained.

Head Coach Stefan Pokorny is convinced of his new signing: "De'Queze Fryer brings exactly the physicality and explosiveness we were looking for at the tight end position. He will add a new dimension to our offense in 2026."

De'Queze Fryer boasts an impressive college career: He played for both Lagrange College and Warner University, earning three All-American selections during that time. Most recently, the 26-year-old played for "the Rebellion" in the IFA, gaining valuable experience.

Despite his past successes, Fryer remains ambitious. "I want to improve every day and consistently make high-level plays," he emphasizes. Personal development is his priority – but team success is even more important to him. His ultimate goal is to contribute to the Graz Giants winning the Austrian Bowl.

Fryer's move to Graz is a conscious decision: "It's another great opportunity to showcase my talent – ​​in a beautiful city with great coaches and strong teammates." He was particularly impressed by the combination of a professional environment and sporting prospects.

With De'Queze Fryer, the Graz Giants gain a versatile, ambitious playmaker who is expected to add extra dynamism to the offense in 2026, expand the existing potential and give the offense more variability.]]></wp:meta_value>
